From: conda-forge
Subject: [PATCH] Disable -threaded for ghc.exe on Windows to avoid builderMainLoop error

The bootstrap GHC on Windows triggers "builderMainLoop: invalid argument"
errors when linking ghc.exe with -threaded. This happens because GHC spawns
multiple processes during linking which fail on Azure CI Windows.

This patch modifies ghc-bin.cabal.in to not use -threaded on Windows,
regardless of the threaded flag setting.

diff --git a/ghc/ghc-bin.cabal.in b/ghc/ghc-bin.cabal.in
--- a/ghc/ghc-bin.cabal.in
+++ b/ghc/ghc-bin.cabal.in
@@ -88,7 +88,10 @@ Executable ghc
     -- mk/config.mk.in logic for GhcThreaded (which ends up
     -- always being True as well). One can still opt out by
     -- disabling this flag.
-    if flag(threaded)
+    -- On Windows, -threaded causes "builderMainLoop: invalid argument" errors
+    -- when the bootstrap GHC spawns processes during linking on Azure CI.
+    -- Disable -threaded on Windows to work around this issue.
+    if flag(threaded) && !os(windows)
       ghc-options: -threaded

     ghc-options: -eventlog
